         <h1>css</h1>
	 <p>A CSS rule consists of a CSS selector and a set of CSS properties. The CSS selector determines what HTML elements to target with the CSS rule. The CSS properties specifies what to style of the targeted HTML elements. ... CSS rules have to be specified inside either a style element or inside an external CSS file and few types of the In a separate file (external)
At the top of a web page document (internal)
Right next to the text it decorates (inline) . This also consits of selectors , functions , animatable, aural , units , color reference , default , browser . </p>
